{"id": 77, "ts": 1778777510.768685, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 3, "agent": "agent_3", "message": "From the attributes I hold, the picture is as follows:\n- **Candidate\u202fA** \u2013 Excellent operational skills (anticipates danger, sees complex connections, strong spatial vision, very good leadership). However, he is described as unfriendly and has unhealthy eating habits. We have no data on his stress\u2011handling ability or his teamwork/communication, both critical for long\u2011haul flights. The lack of any evidence of calmness under pressure or crew interaction is a serious gap.\n- **Candidate\u202fB** \u2013 Very conscientious (reliability) and explicitly handles stress very well (calmness under pressure). He also brings solid technical competence: good weather assessment and excellent computer skills, both valuable for long\u2011distance flight planning and monitoring. The only drawbacks are interpersonal: pretentious attitude, occasional wrong tone, and, as reported by Agent\u202f1, he is uncooperative and grumpy. While these issues affect crew dynamics, they are specific and potentially addressable through crew\u2011resource\u2011management training.\n- **Candidate\u202fC** \u2013 Makes quick, correct decisions and puts concern for others above everything, which supports good crew morale. He also has excellent attention skills. Yet he has difficulty communicating ideas, is regarded as egocentric, and is not very willing to pursue further education. These weaknesses could hinder both day\u2011to\u2011day crew coordination and long\u2011term professional development.\n- **Candidate\u202fD** \u2013 Takes responsibility seriously, solves problems extremely well, concentrates well, and \u201cresponds to unexpected events adequately,\u201d indicating adequate stress handling. He is, however, described as moody and a loner, and we have no information on his teamwork or communication abilities\u2014another critical gap for long\u2011duration operations.\nBalancing the selection criteria\u2014reliability, technical and cognitive competence, calmness under pressure, sound decision\u2011making, teamwork/communication, and long\u2011term suitability\u2014the only candidate with confirmed stress\u2011handling ability and proven reliability is **Candidate\u202fB**. His technical strengths align well with long\u2011distance flight demands, and although his interpersonal style is sub\u2011optimal, the issues are less severe than the unknown stress handling of A, the communication deficits of C, or the moodiness and isolation of D. Therefore, Candidate\u202fB offers the most well\u2011rounded profile for a long\u2011distance pilot.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}"}
