ut his proven reliability and crew\u2011morale contribution address the most safety\u2011critical aspects. Candidate\u202fB\u2019s technical skills are strong, yet his interpersonal deficits are more severe. Candidate\u202fA\u2019s unhealthy habits and resistance to new ideas, and Candidate\u202fD\u2019s moodiness and isolation, further weaken their long\u2011term fit.\nWhen we balance these criteria, Candidate\u202fC offers the strongest overall profile for a long\u2011distance pilot: **absolute reliability, rapid and correct decision\u2011making, and a crew\u2011positive attitude** outweigh the communication difficulty and limited appetite for further education. The other candidates either lack critical reliability evidence (A, D), have serious teamwork deficits (B), or present unknowns in stress handling and crew interaction (A, D).\n**Vote:** Candidate C\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}"}
